OL,6,FHis death was announced in a post on
OL,7,Fhis Facebook page.
OL,9,FA tribute read: "He died doing
OL,10,Fsomething he absolutely wanted to do
OL,11,Fwith a passion and managed to row in
OL,12,Fexcess of 700 miles in the process. An
OL,13,Fachievement in itself."
OL,15,FMichael left Gran Canaria on 27
OL,16,FJanuary, with the voyage expected to
OL,17,Ftake 55 days, and ending in Port St
OL,18,FCharles in Barbados.
